block.p: Demarest Lloyd Quinn and Tate Davis Isenstadt were married yesterday on Cape Cod. Msgr. William A. Genuario performed the ceremony at Our Lady of Victory Church in Centerville, Mass.

Mrs. Quinn-Isenstadt, 26, will begin teaching the first grade at the Dexter School in Brookline, Mass., in September. She graduated from George Washington University and expects to receive a master's degree in elementary education and special education from Manhattanville College later this month. She is the daughter of Tangley DeLaney of Greenwich, Conn., and the late Robert J. Quinn, who lived in Malibu, Calif. Her father was the director of ''The Tonight Show Starring Johnny Carson.'' Her mother is a social worker at Burke Rehabilitation Hospital in White Plains. The bride's stepfather, Robert DeLaney, is a sales associate in the Greenwich office of William Raveis Real Estate.

Mr. Isenstadt, 29, is an assistant manager of the Trade Winds Inn in Craigville, Mass. He graduated from Salve Regina University. He is the son of Christine A. Isenstadt of Boston and Alan Isenstadt of Craigville. His mother owns Model Productions, a recruiting business in Boston. His father owns the Trade Winds Inn.
